He likewise claims housebote and hedgebote in the woods of Kingthorpe, N ewton, Lockton and Ebberston‚ according to the assize of the forest. He pleads that Henry III. granted by deed protection to the House of Sempringham and all houses os the same order, namely, Chicksand, Malton and others. By virtue of which deed he is ready to prove that he and all former Priors and their men have ever been quit of the burdens before mentioned without interruption since the date ofthe deed, and he prays that his claim may be allowed.
